LPI - Lazy Pre Install
======================
LPI is The lazy (best) way to install Arch. It is intended to make it easy to install arch, and do it efficently at that.


How To
------
After you boot from an arch usb, run these commands:
  pacman -Sy git
  git clone https://www.github.com/LordRusk/LPI.git
  ./LPI/lpi.sh
LPI uses slmenu and dash because its efficient, suckless, and easy to work with.


Support
-------
LPI supports EFI and non EFI bios, optional user creation and setting of root password sudoers file editing, installation and enablation of NetworkManager, and installation of xorg-packages for easy wm installation.
